      "explanation_fr": "$1+j+j^2=0$, $j^3=1$. $1+j+\\dots+j^{2023} = \\frac{1-j^{2024}}{1-j}$. $j^{2024}=j^{3\\cdot674+2}=j^2$. Donc somme $= \\frac{1-j^2}{1-j} = 1+j = -j^2 = -\\overline{j} = -j$."
